newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: European feeds see fair trade in rape/sunmeal.
newsitem.headline: European feeds see fair trade in rape/sunmeal.

text.p: The European meals and feeds market saw fair activity this afternoon in EU rapmeal and sunmeal, mostly for positions up to March, market sources said.
Most other products were hardly discussed due to a stronger dollar and a weaker Chicago soymeal futures opening.

"Prompt European rape and sunmeal is relatively expensive and with the current logistical problems because of frozen waterways crushers might have trouble getting seeds and prices could rise further. That caused several buyers to cover positions now," one broker said.
EU rapemeal traded between 31.75 marks per 100 kg fob lower Rhine for this week delivery and 29.50 for March/April.
Feb EU sunmeal changed hands at 21.30 marks per 100 kg fob Amsterdam and at 20.60 marks for Feb/April.
Only one trade was reported in Argentine soymeal pellets at $281 a tonne cif Rotterdam for arrived material, up $1 from yesterday.--KAREL LUIMES +31 20 504 5832
